Edinburgh , Scotland , 10 - 11 September 1999 co-located with VLDB'99 and supported by the Chorochronos network INVITATION TO PARTICIPATE The 1999 Workshop on Spatio- Temporal Database Management , to be held in Edinburgh , Scotland , September 10 - - 11 , 1999 , will bring together researchers in the area of spatio-temporal databases to discuss the state-of-the-art in spatio-temporal research and applications and to understand the new challenges and future research directions in this emerging and rapidly advancing area . . The workshop is slated to serve as a forum for disseminating research and experiences in spatio-temporal databases and for maximizing the interchange of knowledge among researchers from the established spatial and temporal database communities , as well as other related communities . The workshop is spatio-temporally ( ! ) co-located with VLDB'99 , which enables the participants to conveniently attend both events , thereby facilitating the widest possible international participation . The Call for Papers aimed to attract the highest quality and most up-to-date research contributions from around the world . Papers were submitted by authors from fourteen countries and five continents , clearly indicating the international nature of the emerging area of spatio-temporal databases . The Program Committee conducted four reviews of each paper and selected thirteen outstanding papers for presentation and discussion at the workshop and inclusion in the proceedings . The areas covered by the presentations and papers include : . ( i ) understanding and manipulating spatiotemporal data , ( ii ) integration , exchange , and visualization , ( iii ) query processing ( iv ) index evaluation and ( v ) constraints and dependencies . A panel will attempt to define challenges in spatiotemporal database research for the years to come . . We invite you to participate in what promises to be an exciting event . . Babis Theodoulidis , general chair Christian S . Jensen and Michel Scholl , program committee chairs . - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
